# LAYER-1 kit-builder triggering/behavior evals for the `definition-of-done` skill.
# Schema = scripts/validate-evals.mjs: {id, target, prompt, expectation, kind}.
# kind in {positive, near-miss-negative, behavior}. Triggering prompts must NOT
# name the target ("definition-of-done"). DoD = enumerate/confirm the acceptance
# checklist UP FRONT and decide "are we done" against it. The near-miss-negatives
# fence it off from brainstorming (refine fuzzy ask), implementation-planning
# (sequence the build), kit-review/qa (review a finished change), and no-fire
# trivia. Linted for QUALITY only; behavior is judged in the manual Tier-2 loop.

# ---- positives: should load definition-of-done ----
{"id": "dod-pos-build-fully-wired", "target": "definition-of-done", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Build me the saved-views feature fully wired end to end — and I mean fully, no v2 and no deferring bits to later. Lock down what 'done' means before you start.", "expectation": "Loads definition-of-done: produces an enumerated acceptance checklist up front (requirement coverage + a named user-reachable path + companion docs/tests/changelog), confirmed with the arbiter; bakes in the no-deferral rule."}
{"id": "dod-pos-are-we-done", "target": "definition-of-done", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Is this change actually finished, or did we quietly punt something? I want a concrete checklist we can tick off, not a vibe.", "expectation": "Loads definition-of-done: decides done/not-done against an explicit enumerated acceptance checklist — checks requirement coverage, end-to-end reachability, and companion updates — rather than an unfalsifiable judgement."}
{"id": "dod-pos-acceptance-checklist-spec", "target": "definition-of-done", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Before we implement the export-to-CSV capability to spec, write down the acceptance criteria as falsifiable line items so 'every requirement met' is provable and nothing gets shipped half-wired.", "expectation": "Loads definition-of-done: enumerates an up-front, arbiter-confirmable acceptance checklist (coverage, a named user-reachable path, companion artifacts) that makes 'every requirement met' falsifiable; proportional to scope."}

# ---- near-miss-negatives: plausible but must route ELSEWHERE ----
{"id": "dod-near-brainstorm", "target": "definition-of-done", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "The ask is still fuzzy — give me a few options for how we might approach in-app notifications, with the trade-offs and risks, before we commit to anything.", "expectation": "Must NOT load definition-of-done. Correct target: brainstorming — refining a fuzzy request into options/risks, not enumerating an acceptance checklist for a settled build."}
{"id": "dod-near-kit-review", "target": "definition-of-done", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Here's the finished PR — review it before I merge and tell me whether it meets our standards and is safe to land.", "expectation": "Must NOT load definition-of-done. Correct target: kit-review (qa) — reviewing an already-finished change against standards, not setting the up-front acceptance checklist."}
{"id": "dod-near-planning", "target": "definition-of-done", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "We've agreed what to build and what done means — now break it into an ordered, dependency-aware set of steps and tell me what can run in parallel.", "expectation": "Must NOT load definition-of-done. Correct target: implementation-planning — sequencing the build into ordered steps, not defining or confirming the acceptance checklist."}
{"id": "dod-near-adversarial", "target": "definition-of-done", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Red-team this plan and these authored files — find what's missing, fragile, merely asserted, or won't trigger.", "expectation": "Must NOT load definition-of-done. Correct target: adversarial-review — attacking a plan/deliverable for defects, not establishing the acceptance checklist."}
{"id": "dod-near-typo", "target": "definition-of-done", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Fix this typo in the README: 'recieve' should be 'receive'.", "expectation": "Must NOT load definition-of-done. A trivial one-line copy fix needs no acceptance-checklist ceremony — no skill should fire; just make the edit."}

# ---- behavior: once fired, does it produce the right artifact? ----
{"id": "dod-beh-enumerated-checklist", "target": "definition-of-done", "kind": "behavior", "prompt": "Establish what 'done' means for adding a bookmarks capability before we build it, and have me confirm it.", "expectation": "Produces an ENUMERATED, arbiter-confirmed acceptance checklist as discrete line items (not prose) covering all three baked-in families: (a) each requirement has a coverage item, (b) end-to-end reachability — at least one line item names a concrete user-reachable path to the capability (no orphan API-with-no-UI), and (c) companion items for docs/tests/changelog updated in the same effort. Carries the no-deferral/no-v2 rule."}
{"id": "dod-beh-proportional", "target": "definition-of-done", "kind": "behavior", "prompt": "Set the bar for done on this tiny change: bumping a copyright year in the footer.", "expectation": "Proportional output — recognizes the change is trivial and emits a one-line checklist (or equivalently terse confirmation) rather than the full three-family enumeration; does not impose heavyweight ceremony on a trivial change."}
